{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606028"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:07:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:07:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15890"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15890","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15890"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.07,0.7,0.03,0.07,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8581"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71638"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8581","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8581"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15890"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57134"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9847"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20570"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20573"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71638","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71638"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ETwin-to-twin transfusion syndrome is a serious complication that can occur in monochorionic twin pregnancies.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the pathophysiology of twin-to-twin transfusion syndrome?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Blood flows between twins through a shared umbilical cord","Blood flows from one twin to the other through placental anastomoses","Blood mixes between twins through a shared amniotic sac","Blood exchanges between twins through maternal circulation","Blood transfers between twins through direct vessel connections"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ETwin-to-twin transfusion syndrome occurs in monochorionic twin pregnancies when \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood flows from one twin to the other through placental anastomoses\u003C/strong\u003E. This creates an imbalance where one twin (the donor) becomes hypovolaemic and anaemic, while the other twin (the recipient) becomes hypervolaemic and polycythaemic.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EIt is incorrect that \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood flows between twins through a shared umbilical cord\u003C/strong\u003E as each twin has its own umbilical cord. The idea that \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood mixes between twins through a shared amniotic sac\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as blood transfer occurs through the placenta, not the amniotic fluid. \u003Cstrong\u003EBlood transfers between twins through direct vessel connections\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the connections occur in the placenta, not between the twins directly. The concept that \u003Cstrong\u003Eblood exchanges between twins through maternal circulation\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as the transfer occurs through direct placental vessel connections between the twins.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Twin-to-twin transfusion syndrome occurs in monochorionic pregnancies when blood flows from one twin to the other through placental anastomoses, leading to unequal blood distribution.","The recipient twin develops polycythaemia and hypervolaemia while the donor twin becomes anaemic and hypovolaemic."],"references":["Miller JL. Twin to twin transfusion syndrome. Transl Pediatr. 2021 May;10(5):1518-1529. doi: 10.21037/tp-20-264. PMID: 34189110; PMCID: PMC8193008.","Borse V, Shanks AL. Twin-to-Twin Transfusion Syndrome. [Updated 2022 Oct 10]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK563133/","Wagner S, Repke JT, Ural SH. Overview and Long-term Outcomes of Patients Born With Twin-to-Twin Transfusion Syndrome. Rev Obstet Gynecol. 2013;6(3-4):149-54. PMID: 24826204; PMCID: PMC4002191.","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57134"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15890"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57134","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57134"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-19T22:41:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T21:04:16+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8581"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71638"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":